text:
Goooood morning!

1. Quick reminder to runners, joggers, walkers tomorrow for pi race!! We have <@U041S3WQKND> <@U02MANZL55F> <@U02UAQKR56C> <@U040V1EQYMS> <@U01N1775WSU> (virtually), <@U01JYRB9DL2> and me! And <@U041DBXGPC4> signing up soon. I’m going to pick up my shirt today but you can get it tomorrow I believe at 6:30AM! *Race at 7:30AM!!!* Did <@U041PH0B1DF> sign up?
2. Eid Mubarak - as stated by Saeeda above!
3. OMSCS conference in May/ 3-4! 
P.S. totally random but does anybody know any good places to show off my children books? Age 4-8. I created a few and want to share with families but don’t have many friends with kids right now.

Pps for race day people- anybody bringing a car? I forgot I’m doing a hackathon after and have to bring my laptop. Worst case I can jog with it!


---------
EXTRA INFO FOR THE RUNNERS WHO NEED IT:

*Time*
6:30am: Day of race packet pick up and registration
7:30am: Race Start
8:45am: Award Ceremony & Post race celebration

*Location*
The race will start and finish within steps of the Tech Tower Lawn which is where all pre and post-race festivities will happen. <https://www.gtalumni.org/s/1481/images/gid21/editor_documents/pi_mile/microsoftteams-image__2_.png|RACE MAP> & <https://goo.gl/maps/SdjrPrnaxPVFoxpy7|GOOGLE MAP>

*Parking*
Friday, April 21st - Please park in the lower surface Lot (E49) on the east side of the Alumni House and proceed to the Alumni House at 190 North Avenue.

Saturday, April 22nd – Free Race Day parking is available from 5am – 10am in the following areas which can be found on the <https://pts.gatech.edu/sites/default/files/images/gt_parking_zones_map_2_18_20.pdf|GT Parking map>:

E46 Burge Deck
AREA 1 North Avenue Parking Lot
AREA 2 Student Center Visitor Parking
Course map
The 2023 course map is currently being finalized and will be posted here as soon as it has been approved

*Packet Pickup*
EARLY: Friday, 4/21, 10am-5pm- Georgia Tech Alumni Association- <https://www.google.com/maps/place/Georgia+Tech+Alumni+Association/@33.7717326,-84.3954596,18z/data=!4m5!3m4!1s0x88f5048a8c05743b:0x17ddf4ecc35ff171!8m2!3d33.7710243!4d-84.393511?shorturl=1|MAP>
- Please park in Visitor area 1- <https://www.google.com/maps/place/Visitor+Area+1/@33.7717221,-84.3954386,18.02z/data=!4m5!3m4!1s0x88f50462c3f3cee5:0xe0dbe96335dc0d29!8m2!3d33.7710066!4d-84.3944944?shorturl=1|MAP>
RACE DAY: Saturday, 4/22, 6:30-7:15am, Tech Tower Lawn- <https://www.google.com/maps/place/Tech+Tower+Lawn/@33.7717326,-84.396554,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m5!3m4!1s0x88f50462ef6f0bb5:0x8baa29b73178dc8d!8m2!3d33.7717326!4d-84.3943653?shorturl=1|MAP>

*Hydration*
The 5k course will have one aid station at approximately the halfway point.

*Awards*
Awards will be presented in the following categories:
- Overall male/ Overall female
- 1st place Alumni male/female
- 1st place Faculty/Staff male/female
- 1st place Student male/female
- Top Team (based on participation)
- Top three finishers in each of the following age groups (M/F)
-9 & Under, 10-14, 15-19, 20-29, 30-39, 40-49, 50-59, 60-69, 70+
(Virtual participants are not eligible for awards)
-------

Have a great finals week!!
Cherie Lum
